    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1087"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4015.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am reliably informed that at present there are some 1,500 Americans still
                    Mexico City, many having just arrived from surrounding <pb facs="0796" n="680"
                        xml:id="pg_680"/> country. My informant states that many of these Americans
                    are desirous of leaving for Vera Cruz but understand the train which left night
                    before last was last opportunity. In view of this have telegraphed Brazilian
                    Minister and also communicated with Admiral Craddock requesting that steps be
                    taken and arrangements be made for the transportation of all those who will
                    leave to Vera Cruz as soon as possible. As we understand Department in direct
                    communication Mexico City, respectfully suggest Department also take this matter
                    up.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
